HEADWORD: Wellingtonia
<hw>Wel`ling*to"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. So named
after the Duke of <etsep>Wellington</etsep>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A name given to the ⟦ldquo⟧big trees⟦rdquo⟧ (<spn>Sequoia
gigantea</spn>) of California, and still used in England. See
<er>Sequoia</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

